deck: A magician above reproach, a darling of London high society, and consulting exorcist to the Secret Intelligence Service
description:
Origin

A student at Cambridge who studied the occult, Georgie Snow met John Constantine when she and her girlfriend Veronica Delacroix were attending a demonic punk show in Manchester. Distrustful of his methods and angered when Veronica chose Constantine over her, Georgie retreated to her studies. Distinguishing herself in her field, she eventually became consulting exorcist to Her Majesty's Secret Service.

Creation

Georgie Snow was created by James Tynion IV, Ming Doyle, and Vanesa R Del Rey. She made her first appearance in Constantine: The Hellblazer #3.

Major Story Arcs

The Hellblazer

Working on an apparent incubus infestation in England, Georgie is approached by Constantine, who offers to help despite her strenuous objections and their difficult shared past. She watches Constantine attempt to infiltrate the lair of the incubus Meridian, which he has misidentified as a succubus, and saves him when the incubus attacks him. He is able to convince her to help him exorcise the vengeance monster that has been stalking him, neglecting to inform her that the monster is actually the twisted soul of Veronica. She successfully exorcises the creature, and angrily severs ties with Constantine. Despite this, she agrees to conduct part of a ritual designed to loosen Neron's hold on New York City.

Powers and Abilities

Georgie is an exorcist and occultist of great talent and skill. She is very intelligent, and well-educated in the area of the occult.
name: Georgiana Snow
